<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449432" target="top">Kebilal</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=graalthedorf>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/14/03 10:46:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: haha BPs</span><hr size=1> Couple of responses to that:<br>
<br>
Firstly, I guess you weren't aware of it, but paladins can't cast KEI. Yes, it is fairly ubiquitous, but you can't simply claim that all paladins will have it all the time.<br>
<br>
Secondly, yes it is much easier to get aggro as a paladin or shadow knight. Does that necessarily mean that there is an imbalance? No it does not. You can argue that it does and provide meaningful points supporting that argument, but it hasn't been made yet.<br>
<br>
As several people have said here, groups simply take the first tank that is available. There are exceptions, of course. The vast majority of those exceptions are to the benefit of warriors. I think I asked you a question once and you hemmed and hawwed without answering: Have you ever heard of an experience group say &quot;We can't do that, we don't have a (paladin/shadow knight)&quot;? Have you ever heard of a raid break up because there were no paladins or shadowknights there?<br>
<br>
At the very high levels fighting against very high damage output mobs, efficiency in tanking generally isn't as important as whether the tank can survive between heals. Anything that is borderline hard for a warrior without defensive is going to be undoable for a knight of the same level of gear. Add in defensive and there are many situations in which a knight simply can NOT do the tanking of a warrior with markedly inferior gear. Some of those situations are with normal experience groups...at least the ones that push the limit. Generally, you can't just take a lesser tank and just take a hit to efficiency...you simply can't do the task. I'd be happy if I could tank vindi with the same amount of clerics as a lesser equipped warrior and the only difference would be greater downtime afterward.<br>
<br>
Is the aggro advantage of knights too much of a counterbalance to warrior's tanking superiority? I don't know. I do know that warriors simply are NOT having problems getting groups relative to the other plate class tanks. That is an enormous fallacy. I KNOW what it is like to not be able to find groups. I remember many times seeing a group shouting for a tank, sending a tell &quot;level X paladin&quot; and getting told &quot;I said tank, not paladin&quot;. There is actual parity for once in tanking for xp groups. I'm sorry you guys aren't happy with that. Maybe things have changed drastically in the 2 and a half months since I last played, but I doubt it.<br>
<br>
Zone into PoV, /ooc camp check, take down the names that answer. Send a tell to one person from each group and ask who is tanking for them. I bet if you did that enough times you find a pretty evenly spread mix warrior, shadowknight, paladin. If an even spread isn't good enough for you, too damn bad.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
