<br>
Chavr on PoN says he typically casts one or two stuns per battle.  And he also claims that allowing Warriors to have the equivalent of one stun's worth of aggro at the beginning of a fight would be completely impossible because it would doom Paladins to oblivion, never to be grouped again.<br>
<br>
Now, you're telling me Paladins are casting a lot more stuns per battle than Chavr claims, who insists that one stun's worth of aggro is far too much for Warriors.  How, preytell, to you balance that the effective aggro of one stun is too much when Paladins are casting more than two stuns per battle to maintain aggro?  Something doesn't jive here.<br>
<br>
You can't on the one hand say, oh Warriors can't have the aggro of one stun, because Paladins typically don't cast more than one or two stuns per battle and then say, oh Paladins are using a lot more mana per battle than two stuns and so we don't have anywhere near the mana you think we do.  These are contradicting points.  They can't both be true at the same time, now can they?  It's one or the other.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Does that necessarily mean that there is an imbalance? No it does not. You can argue that it does and provide meaningful points supporting that argument, but it hasn't been made yet.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It is your perception that the points haven't been made.  It is mine that they have, repeatedly.  Over and over again.  Until people are blue in the face.  You refuse to listen or believe?  Fine, you can do that.  But don't expect us to trot out the evidence yet again when you refused to believe us the first dozen times.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Add in defensive and there are many situations in which a knight simply can NOT do the tanking of a warrior with markedly inferior gear. Some of those situations are with normal experience groups...at least the ones that push the limit.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Graal, you're an intelligent dorf, I'll give you that.  But do you realize how completely specious this arguement is?  There is a ten minute timer on defensive, I'm sure you know this.  Three minutes of effectiveness with 7 minutes of unavailability.  I find it hard to believe that anyone is doing an experience camp with the intention of only killing for 3 minutes out of every 10.  I've never hunted like this.  No one I know does an experience camp like this.  Most people would be horrified to even consider killing for 3 minutes out of every ten.  What are you thinking?  This makes no sense at all.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I do know that warriors simply are NOT having problems getting groups relative to the other plate class tanks. That is an enormous fallacy.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Thanks for clearing up our misperceptions about not being able to find a group.  I thought my personal experiences might have some relevance, but now that you've explained it to me, Paladin to Warrior, that I'm not having any trouble finding a group, it's all much clearer now.  Gosh, how have I gotten along before now without you to set me straight?<br>
