<br>
So we are happily exp'ing along with war, cle, shm, mon, rog, enc when we decide to split off an irmin and try him out.  Our monk was a great splitter so we peeled off one of the warrior irmins.  The first hit he did to me I mashed down hard on my DEFENSIVE key and proceeded to live through the encounter.<br>
<br>
We decided to do this a few more times as the night progressed we all got a giant head and nearly all of us got a sash WOOT !<br>
<br>
Keep in mind I was wearing a 40 AC tunic and 22 AC legs (I'm not a twink and I only have SS gloves and 2 SS bracers and SS arms - still in cobalt boots too).<br>
<br>
Find me one pally or SK that could have tanked one of those giants every 10 to 15 minutes without dying and IN CRAPPY GEAR <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and I'll show you someone that was chain runed and used the full 100% of the cleric's mana.<br>
<br>
*Disclaimer :  The preceeding situation was meant to illustrate the potential of a low 60's group with a 62 war to push themselves to the limit in a normal exp'ing situation.  At know time were any animals hurt during the production of this text.<br>
<br>
Now this is just one of hundreds of situations (both in exp groups and MOST DEFINITELY on raids) where a warrior can do what no paladin or SK can do - tank above his normal limits and do it with style, never dying, and saving the cleric mana in the process while allowing the group to achieve kills they never could have hoped to achieve without the warrior.<br>
<br>
NOTE :  Before you try to tell me that a paladin or SK could tank one of those irmin every 10 to 15 minutes and the group would still be able to kill 3 or 4 additional &quot;normal&quot; exp mobs between the downtime of the defensive disc.... let me remind you that the irmin warrior-type mobs double (and possibly triple, not sure) for 710 damage.  Please consider this if you have never actually played a level 62 knight at this camp or witnessed this happen.<br>
<br>
I'm betting it simply isn't possible - remember we pulled several (about 10) of these irmin that night and never had a party wipe.<br>
<br>
Food for thought - as always, your milage may vary.<br>
<br>
Warriors are tanks - that's all we can do.  We cannot heal the party or add to attack, AC, HP, mana.  If we are removed from our position as tanks that would be like making a rogue fight hand to hand only or taking the FD skill away from a monk.  We are tanks - so let us tank and stop trying to beat into our heads that we are broken.  We are not broken.<br>
<br>
If we are broken, then the pally's and SK's that cannot tank an irmin at level 62 are also broken.  Let's all go tell them how bad they suck cause they can't tank Vindi or push an exp group beyond its &quot;normal constraints&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
