You cover this point in your own post, just three paragraphs down. At the moment, in Planes of Power, the superior agro of knights offsets the advantages of having a warrior<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;There are exceptions, of course. The vast majority of those exceptions are to the benefit of warriors. I think I asked you a question once and you hemmed and hawwed without answering: Have you ever heard of an experience group say &quot;We can't do that, we don't have a (paladin/shadow knight)&quot;? Have you ever heard of a raid break up because there were no paladins or shadowknights there?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, yes. I have seen 3 raids break up due to a lack of paladins and Shadowknights. Emperor Ssra and High Priest are two encounters that require add-tanks with the ability to sustain agro without dealing damage. As it so happens, Knights are far better at doing this than warriors, to the extent that warriors simply cannot do this job. Believe me, I've tried. Add-tanking without dealing damage means that the mob switched onto healing clerics constantly.<br>
<br>
Yes, I'll consent that warriors who serve as tanks for raids have a locked down role at a raid. However, warriors not tanking bring far less to a raid than a knight. So, yes, a certain amount of warriors have a set spot on a raid. however, a knight is a more usefull addition to a raid than a non-tanking warrior<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;At the very high levels fighting against very high damage output mobs, efficiency in tanking generally isn't as important as whether the tank can survive between heals. Anything that is borderline hard for a warrior without defensive is going to be undoable for a knight of the same level of gear. Add in defensive and there are many situations in which a knight simply can NOT do the tanking of a warrior with markedly inferior gear. Some of those situations are with normal experience groups...at least the ones that push the limit. Generally, you can't just take a lesser tank and just take a hit to efficiency...you simply can't do the task. I'd be happy if I could tank vindi with the same amount of clerics as a lesser equipped warrior and the only difference would be greater downtime afterward&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
/Disc defensive doesn't get used very often in XP group scenarios. MObs fought in XP groups generally don't require the ability. In an S-O-S scenario, it gets used, kind of like paladin LoH. Efficiency in tanking may not be important, but you damn well better believe that snap agro is.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;Warriors DO have issues... this much I and most experienced hybrids will agree with... and aggro is one of them... I would love to see warriors have some additional ability to add numerical hate that isnt linked to the taunt button. (say perhaps KICK)&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you read carefully, you will see that this is the exact claim currently made by warriors in regards to balance. My personal idea is a separate taunt button on a 45 second refresh that give a certain amount of agro.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Wilhelmm D'averam<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Overlord of the Apocalypse</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
