I am OOM quite often while uber-taunting... I am not a Paladin expert, but I know for certain that throwing a Darkness or even TWO does not lock aggro.... (especially when its resisted... or mob is immune to movement spells)  The type of aggro control you are taling about is good enough to hold a mob perhaps...  but not LOCK (meaning no matter WHAT is done outside of you...) <br>
<br>
A Shadowknight uses the taunt button very often in this case to grab aggro back just like a warrior should...  a warrior with EB weapons will garner the same aggro or greater aggro with only a moment's pause for the party....  (pre-aggro will never be the warrior's strong suit, as they have no method of garnering aggro at range save for bow damage) permanent LOCK on aggro is only acheived through correct and consistent timing of spells and taunt button useage.  oh, and just for your information, Shadowknights have NO mana cost reductions via AAXP.<br>
<br>
In comparison with a Paladin at my level and in similar gear, Stun and Dark aggro seems similar (neither of us has numbers as we have no way to compare except snap aggro)  Both stun and dark are sometime used against immune mobs...  both of them seem similar in aggro component when reisted or immune...  terror of Thule (100hate/cast less than EB) causes considerably more hate than a resisted/immune snare... and this would be comparable to stun....<br>
<br>
On top of this, everything knights are depend VERY heavily on mana...  note that while uber taunting, I am NOT dealing warrior-level damage (not even warrior from-the-front damage) and I am not as good at taking damage as a warrior and cannot lifetap much...  I am thus giving up everything to be able to taunt the best in the game...  this sounds balanced to me.<br>
